                     Full Committee Markups and Meetings

     * December 19,  2001
          + House passed H.R. 3529, the "Economic Security and Worker
            Assistance Act of 2001."  Ways and Means did not act on this
            legislation.
     * December 12,  2001
          + House passed H. Con. Res. 282, the "Keeping the Social
            Security Promise Initiative."  Ways and Means did not act on
            this legislation.
     * December 4,  2001
          + House passed H.R. 3391, the "Medicare Regulatory and
            Contracting Reform Act of 2001."  Ways and Means did not act
            on this legislation.
          + House passed H.R. 3346,  a bill to amend the Internal Revenue
            Code of 1986 to simplify the reporting requirements relating
            to higher education tuition and related expenses.  Passed
            Senate December 20, 2001.  Ways and Means did not act on this
            legislation.
          + House passed H.R. 3323, the "Administrative Simplification
            Compliance Act."  Passed Senate December 12, 2001.
            P.L. 107-105.  Ways and Means did not act on this legislation.
     * November 28,  2001
          + House passed H.R. 2722, the "Clean Diamond Trade Act."  Ways
            and Means did not act on this legislation.
     * November 16, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 3210, the "Terrorism Risk Protection Act" -
            Action Release., H. Rept. 107-300, Part 2, H.R. 3210, as
            reported.  Click on the links for copies of markup documents:
            Chairman's amendment in the nature of a substitute to H.R.
            3210, Description of Chairman's Amendment (JCX-82-01).
     * November 7, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 2269, the Retirement Security Advice Act of
            2001  -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-262, part 2, H.R. 2269,
            as reported. Click on the links for copies of markup
            documents: Chairman Thomas' amendment in the nature of a
            substitute, H.R. 2269, as reported by the Committee on
            Education and the Workforce, and Joint Committee on Taxation
            website for Description of the Chairman's amendment in the
            nature of a substitute to H.R. 2269 (JCX-73-01), and Estimated
            Revenue Effects of a Chairman's amendment in the nature of a
            substitute to H.R. 2269 (JCX-74-01).
          + House passed H. Con. Res. 252, Expressing the Sense of
            Congress, that the President at the WTO round of negotiations,
            should preserve the ability of the United States to enforce
            rigorously its trade laws by other countries.  Referred to
            Ways and Means, but not considered.
     * November 6, 2001
          + House Passed S. 1447, the "Aviation Security Act."  (S. 1447
            passed the House in lieu of H.R. 3150.).  P.L. 107-71.
     * October 31, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 2873, the "Safe and Stable Families Amendments
            of 2001"  Action Release.  H. Rept. 107-281, to accompany H.R.
            2873, as reported.  Passed the Senate December 13, 2001.
            Cleared for President.  Click on the links for copies of
            markup documents:  H.R. 2873, as reported by the Human
            Resources Subcommittee; Subcommittee Report on H.R. 2873; and
            H.R. 2873, Summary of Changes Reflected in Thomas/Herger
            Amendment in the Nature of a Substitute to H.R. 2873 the
            "Promoting Safe and Stable Families Amendments of 2001," and
          + Markup of H.R. 3129, the "Customs Border Security Act of
            2001." Action Release., H. Rept. 107-320, part 1, part 2, part
            3 part 4, H.R. 3129, as reported, Floor amendment. Click on
            the links for copies of markup documents:  Explanation of H.R.
            3129, and Description of Modifications to H.R. 3129 Contained
            in Chairman's Amendment in the Nature of a Substitute.
     * October 23,  2001
          + House passed H.R. 2899, the "War Bonds Act of 2001: Ways and
            Means was discharged.  Awaiting Senate action.
     * October 12, 2001
          + Mark up of H.R. 3090, the "Economic Security and Recovery Act
            of 2001" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-251.  Click on the
            links for a copies of markup documents:  Chairman's amendment
            in the nature of a substitute, Summary of Health Care
            Provisions for the Unemployed, and the Summary of Unemployment
            Compensation Provision.  Visit the Joint Committee on Taxation
            Website for a Description of H.R. 3090 and a Description of
            the Amendment in the Nature of a Substitute.
     * October 11, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 2768, the "Medicare Regulatory and Contracting
            Reform Act of 2001" -- Action Release. H. Rept. 107-288,  to
            accompany  H.R. 2768, as reported.  Click on the links for
            copies of markup documents:  Chairman Thomas' amendment in the
            nature of a substitute; Summary of Changes in Chairman Thomas'
            Substitute; Subcommittee on Health Report accompanying H.R.
            2768, and H.R. 2768, as reported by the Subcommittee.
     * October 9, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 3005, the "Bipartisan Trade Promotion Authority
            Act of 2001" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-249, part 1,
            Manager's Amendment, Explanation of Manager's Amendment.
            Click on the links for copies of markup documents: Summary of
            H.R. 3005; Side-by-Side Comparison;  Summary of Agricultural
            Provisions;  Summary of  Consultation with Congress
            Provisions; and  Summary of Labor and Environment Provisions.
     * October 5, 2001
          + Markup of H.R.3008, the a bill to reauthorize the trade
            adjustment assistance program under the Trade Act of 1974.  --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 107-244, Floor Amendment. Explanation
            of H.R. 3008.
          + Markup of H.R. 3010, a bill to amend the Trade Act of 1974 to
            extend the Generalized System of Preferences until December
            31, 2002. -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-245.  Click on the
            links for copies of documents:  Summary of H.R. 3010; and
          + Markup of H.R. 3009, the "Andean Trade Promotion and Drug
            Eradication Act;" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-290, to
            accompany H.R. 3009, as reported.  Click on the links for
            copies of markup documents:  Summary of H.R. 3009, Amendment
            in the Nature of a Substitute; and Description of
            Modifications to H.R. 3009.
     * September 21,  2001
          + House and Senate passed H.R. 2926, the "Air Transportation
            Safety and System Stabilization Act."  P.L. 107-42.
            Ways and Means was discharged.
     * September 13, 2001
          + House passed H.R. 2884, the "Victims of Terrorism Relief Act
            of 2001: Ways and Means was discharged.  House agreed to
            Senate amendment to House amendment to Senate amendment on
            December 20, 2001.
     * August 2, 2001
          + House passed H.R. 2563, the "Bipartisan Patient Protection
            Act." Ways and Means was discharged.  Awaiting conference
            action with the Senate.
          + House passed H.R. 4, the "SAFE Act of 2001."  Ways and Means
            was discharged.  Provisions of  H.R. 2511, were incorporated
            in the bill.
     * July 26, 2001
          + Markup of H.J. Res. 51, a joint resolution approving the
            extension of nondiscriminatory treatment with respect to the
            products of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam -- Action
            Release, H. Rept. 107-198, P.L. 107-52.   Click on the links
            for accompanying documents:  Explanation of H.J. Res. 51;
            Summary of U.S.-Vietnam Bilateral Trade Agreement
          + Markup of H.R. 2603, "United States-Jordan Free Trade Area
            Implementation Act of 2001" -- Action Release, H. Rept.
            107-176, Part 1, P.L. 107-43.   Click on the links for
            accompanying documents:  Description of  H.R. 2603;
            Description of the Chairman's amendment.
     * July 23, 2001
          + House Passed S. 1190, a bill to amend the Internal Revenue
            Code of 1986 to rename the education individual retirement
            accounts as the Coverdell education savings account.  P.L.
            107-22.
     * July 18, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 2511, the "Energy Tax Policy Act of 2001" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 107-157.  See H.R. 4 above for
            further action.
     * July 11, 2001
          + Markup of H.J. Res. 50, a joint resolution disapproving the
            extension of the waiver authority contained in section 402(c)
            of the Trade Act of 1974 with respect to the People's Republic
            of China -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-145, H.J. Res. 50, as
            reported, Explanation of H.J. Res. 50
          + Markup of H.J. Res. 55, a joint resolution disapproving the
            extension of the waiver authority contained in section 402(c)
            of the Trade Act of 1974 with respect to Vietnam -- Action
            Release, H.Rept. 107-154, H.J. Res. 55, as reported,
            Explanation of
            H.J. Res. 55
          + Markup of H.R. 1954, the "ILSA Extension Act of 2001" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 107-107, Part 2, P.L. 107-24.
     * July 11, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 7, the "Community Solutions Act of 2001." --
            Action Release,  H. Rept. 107-138, Part 2, H.R. 7, as
            reported, H.R. 7 substitute, considered as adopted upon
            adoption of the rule
     * May 16, 2001
          + House passed H.R. 1836, the "Economic Growth and Tax Relief
            Reconciliation Act of 2001."   The bill was referred to the
            Committee but was not marked up.  Provisions from H.R. 3, H.R.
            6, H.R. 8, H.R. 10, H.R. 586, and H.R. 622 were included in
            the conference report to accompany H.R. 1836, H. Rept.107-84,
            P.L. 107-16.  For a summary of the report, go to Joint
            Committee on Taxation's Website.  Read the Release.  Click on
            the links for additional summary information, and tax rebate
            information,  Chairman Thomas at Tax Bill Signing Ceremony
     * May 9, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 622, the "Hope for Children Act" -- Action
            Release,  H. Rept. 107-64 (For further action, see H.R. 1836
            above)
          + H.R. 586, the "Fairness for Foster Care Families Act of 2001"
            -- Action Release,    H. Rept. 107-66.  (For further action,
            see H.R. 1836 above)
          + H.R. 1727, the "Fallen Hero Survivor Benefit Fairness Act of
            2001"  -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-65, P.L. 107-15
     * April 25, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 10, the "Comprehensive Retirement Security and
            Pension Reform Act of 2001" -- Action Release. H. Rept.
            107-51, Part 1.  (For further action, see H.R. 1836 above)
     * March 29, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 8, the "Death Tax Elimination Act of 2001" --
            Action Release, H. Rept. 107-37.  (For further action, see
            H.R. 1836 above)
     * March 22, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 6, the "Marriage Penalty and Family Tax Relief
            Act of 2001" -- Action Release, H. Rept. 107-29.  (For further
            action, see H.R. 1836 above)
     * March 14, 2001
          + Approval of Views and Estimates Letter -- Action Release.
     * March 1, 2001
          + Markup of H.R. 3, the "Economic Growth and Tax Relief Act of
